2. Commentary completeness

Compare regulatory_information and compliance_assessment
pointer-by-pointer.

If any requirement pointer appears missing,
mention that pointer.

Examples:
para 3.2 missing
section 4(b) not covered
clause 5 not addressed

Do not list all pointers.
Only report missing ones.



3. Support for conclusion

Check if the conclusion in compliance_assessment
is supported by evidence.

If a pointer is not supported by evidence,
mention that pointer.

Use short identifiers if available.



4. Reference traceability

Check if evidence references are specific.

Mark Unclear if reference is generic.

Examples:
policy name only
no section cited
no clause
no date
no version

Mention briefly what is missing.



5. Follow-up clarity (only if Non-Compliant / Partial / Adverse)

If compliance_status is Non-Compliant, Partial, or Adverse,
check return_to_compliance_plan.

If action is missing or unclear,
mention the gap or pointer.

